did.head: Descriptive Summary

physdesc.label: Collection Size
physdesc.extent: 384 manuscript boxes, 7 card file boxes, 2 oversize boxes, 1 cubic foot box, 42 envelopes, 2 albums

did.abstract: Correspondence, speeches and writings, memoranda, notes, clippings, printed matter, and photographs, relating to American politics, American neutrality in World Wars I and II, military conscription in the United States, New Deal social and economic legislation, the Supreme Court controversy of 1937, the Progressive movement in the United States, and the Minnesota Farmer-Labor Party.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: The Hoover Institution Archives only allows access to copies of audiovisual items. To listen to sound recordings or to view videos or films during your visit, please contact the Archives at least two working days before your arrival. We will then advise you of the accessibility of the material you wish to see or hear. Please note that not all audiovisual material is immediately accessible.

scopecontent.p: Family, business, personal, congressional, and constituent correspondence arranged first chronologically, then alphabetically either by last name of correspondent or by initial of name of company or institution, and occasionally by subject matter or physical form. General correspondence is in Boxes 1-61, 70, and 166-218; correspondence and reference files about federal and state agencies are in Boxes 71-72; and constituent mail is in Boxes 62-69, 73-89 (includes some correspondence with clients and friends), 90-94 (re conscription during World War I), 95-101 (re U.S. Supreme Court), 102-139, 140-162 (re conscription during World War II, U.S. neutrality, and repeal of the 1937 embargo to discourage sale of arms to Spain during the Spanish Civil War), and 163-165

Notes, memoranda, pamphlets, clippings, correspondence, newsletters, articles, maps, charts, reports arranged alphabetically by subject. This file postdates Senator Lundeen's death because Mrs. Lundeen added material to various subjects

Biographies, family genealogies, correspondence, financial records, legal documents, lists, memberships, reports, schedules, clippings, other printed matter arranged alphabetically by subject or physical form. Some files about Mrs. Lundeen are included
Campaign literature, clippings, research materials, speeches, and correspondence describing candidates and issues in local or national elections. Arranged first chronologically, then by physical form
Memoranda, reports, office finances and personnel, minutes, pamphlets, press releases, itineraries, calls to committee meetings, clippings and miscellany arranged alphabetically by subject
Office docket, legal documents, financial records and correspondence arranged alphabetically by physical form
Research materials, drafts and printed copies of bills and correspondence arranged chronologically
Drafts and printed copies of speeches, debates, articles, notes and background materials arranged chronologically
Index cards of names of campaign workers, political supporters and non-supporters filed alphabetically and miscellaneous files unsorted
Political campaign broadsides, an election certificate, clipping scrapbooks, a poem, and a tribute to Lundeen
Checkbooks, check stubs, bank statements, bills and receipts
1363 prints, 58 post cards and 2 albums depicting Ernest Lundeen and others including family members, friends, political colleagues, and views of Hawaii and the Soviet Union
